item.title: Running Server Dosent Load With No-ip
item.dc:creator: @thugscape thugscape
item.description:
@thugscape wrote:

If you have problems port forwarding your router try using uttorent. Ill show you the steps to portforward with utorent.
Step 1. Go to google and lookup utorrent click first link and download it.
Step 2. After downloading run your scource, then open up no-ip.
Step 3. After opening no-ip run utorrent. Go to options. Click prefrences. Under general settings click connection ucheck upnp port mapping.
Step 4. Change the port to 43594. Click apply.
Then loggin with your no-ip account. if this doesnt work. here is a list of possible reasons.

  1. You might have your ip hidden.
  2. Try restarting your browser.
  3. You may have to many things open close everything that you do not need open to portforward.
    If these to not work pm me and i will help you as much as i can.
    Your welcome
    Thugscape[br][br][size=1]Posted on: March 04, 2009, 03:19:56 am[/size][hr]Ok. If you have teamviewer pm me. And i will fix it.
    Plus i think ur hiding ur ip is the problem.
